summary: An email from an FBI agent in New York to FBI agent Paul Byrne, introducing a fellow Quantico classmate who is an agent in West Palm Beach and has possible information on the Epstein case. The email provides the West Palm agent's contact number.

persons.name: Paul Byrne
persons.context: Recipient of an email from a New York FBI agent regarding a West Palm Beach FBI agent with possible information on the Epstein case.

connections.description: Colleagues within the FBI; the NY agent is reaching out to Byrne with a lead.
Connected via the NY agent; the West Palm agent is a Quantico classmate of the NY agent and has possible case information.
Quantico classmates; the NY agent is facilitating contact regarding the Epstein case.

events.title: Email regarding Epstein case lead
events.description: An FBI agent in New York emails Paul Byrne to introduce a Quantico classmate, an agent in West Palm Beach, who has possible information on the Epstein case.

keyFacts: The email is dated July 13, 2019, shortly after Jeffrey Epstein's arrest on July 6, 2019.
An FBI agent in West Palm Beach reportedly has possible information on the Epstein case.
The communication shows internal FBI coordination regarding the Epstein investigation.
The West Palm Beach agent is identified as a Quantico classmate of the sending New York agent.
